cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.CL 

This paper discusses evaluation metrics for ranking systems in information retrieval and Web search, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed methodology involves learning gain values and discount factors from user preferences, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions user preferences, which suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
